5️⃣ (Optional) Clean‑up old backup directories
Once you’ve confirmed everything works and you no longer need the backup copies, you can delete them to free space:

bash

# Delete any backup folder older than 30 days (adjust as you like)
find $HOME -maxdepth 1 -type d -name "*.backup.*" -mtime +30 -exec rm -rf {} +
If you want to keep them for a while, just leave them; they’re harmless.

TL;DR – One‑Line Command (if you’re comfortable)
If you want to do everything in a single shot (backup‑list, restore, restart, health‑check), you can run this concatenated command. Read it first – it does exactly what the step‑by‑step above does.


# Stop, restore from newest backup, start, then health‑check
~/openwebui-manager/stop-all.sh && sleep 5 && \
for name in testwebui openwebui2ver7 openwebui3 testwebui-v10 openwebui2ver7-v10 openwebui4; do \
  b=$(ls -dt "${HOME}/${name}.backup"* 2>/dev/null | head -n1); \
  if [ -n "$b" ]; then \
    cp -a "${b}/.webui_secret_key" "${HOME}/${name}/" 2>/dev/null; \
    rm -rf "${HOME}/${name}/data"; \
    cp -a "${b}/data" "${HOME}/${name}/"; \
    echo "✅ Restored $name from $b"; \
  else echo "⚠️ No backup for $name"; fi; \
done && \
~/openwebui-manager/start-all.sh && sleep 30 && \
~/openwebui-manager/health-all.sh
What to do next if something still isn’t right
Symptom
What to check
You’re asked to create a new account after the restart
Verify that the file ${HOME}/<instance>/.webui_secret_key exists and contains a long base‑64 string (not empty). If it’s missing, copy it from the backup as shown above.
Model selector still forgets after refresh
Open the developer console (F12 → Console) on that port, change the model, and look for any red error messages (e.g. localStorage quota, CORS, or indexedDB errors). Paste the first few lines here.
Chat history is still empty
Run du -sh ~/openwebui2ver7/data/* (and the other instances) to see if the backup data folder still contains webui.db and subfolders like uploads/, vector_db/, etc. If those files are present, the restore script should have copied them; otherwise the backup may have been removed.


